# strings.iron expected-scopes reference.
Token               | Scope
--------------------|--------------------------------
"hello"             | string.quoted.double.iron
"line\n"            | string.quoted.double.iron (containing constant.character.escape.iron for \n)
$"value is ${...}"  | string.interpolated.iron (containing meta.interpolation.iron for ${...})

Covers UI-SPEC S6: string.quoted.double.iron, string.interpolated.iron,
meta.interpolation.iron (nested), constant.character.escape.iron.

The interpolated-string pattern uses begin/end delimiter pairs at both
levels — reviewed per CONTEXT D-02 specifics (no nested unbounded
quantifiers; safe-regex lint green).
